\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 6. S. crassifolius} Pourret ex Willd.,{\i  Sp. Pl.}{\b  3}: 1509 (1803). Perennial; stem 10-40 cm, simple, glabrous. Leaves glabrous, auriculate, entire to pinnatifid, irregularly spinose-dentate, the lower spathulate, the upper oblong to oblong-elliptical, the uppermost triangular-ovate. Capitula axillary and terminal, subsessile. Involucral bracts c. 35. Ligules about as long as corolla-tube. Achenes 2-3 × 1-1·4 mm, elliptical to oblong-elliptical, rugose between the ribs; pappus 7-10 mm, persistent. {\i Damp saline or calcareous soils. • C. & E. Spain.} Hs.
