\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 7. S. arvensis} L.,{\i  Sp. Pl.} 793 (1753). Perennial, far-creeping; stem 30-150 cm, simple or branched. Leaves glabrous, with dentate margins, the lower entire to pinnatipartite with triangular lobes, the upper larger, pinnatipartite to pinnatisect, with rounded, often dentate auricles. Capitula terminal, pedunculate. Involucral bracts 38-50. Ligules about as long as corolla-tube. Achenes 2·5-3·5 × 1-1·5 mm, elliptical, rugose between the ribs; pappus 10-14 mm, persistent. 2n = 36, 54. {\i Cultivated and waste ground, and on maritime sands and shingle. Throughout Europe except for parts of the south-west and some of the islands.} Al Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fa Fe Ga Ge Gr Hb He Ho Hs Hu It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, B, C, W, K, E) Sa Su Tu.
