\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 8. S. pustulatus} Willk. in Willk. & Lange,{\i  Prodr. Fl. Hisp.}{\b  2}: 242 (1865). Perennial; stem 15-30 cm, branched, woody and with greyish-yellow bark below. Lower leaves few, the upper grouped below inflorescence, white-tomentose at base, pinnatisect, with ovate to elliptical, entire lobes. Involucral bracts c. 24. Ligules about twice as long as corolla-tube. Achenes 3·5-5 × 1·5 mm, narrowly rectangular or more or less elliptical, often curved, slightly rugose between the ribs; pappus c. 8 mm, most of the long hairs deciduous and the short cottony ones persistent.{\i  Calcareous rocks. S.E. Spain} ({\i near Almeria}). Hs. ({\i N.W. Africa.})
