\pard\f0\fs28 Annual to perennial herbs. Stem usually solitary, branched. Leaves entire to pinnatifid, often prickly. Capitula few to numerous. Involucre cylindrical; bracts in several rows. Receptacle without scales. Ligules yellow or bluish. Achenes compressed, beaked, usually with ribs; pappus of 2 equal rows of simple hairs.
\par 

\par 

\pard\f0\fs28  In the descriptions of achenes, the length includes the beak, and the number of ribs is given for one side.
